{
  "texts": [
    "Since LLMs are impressive, easy-to-use yet potentially brittle tools, under what conditions can researchers safely plug-in their outputs into empirical research?",
    "In this section, we develop a framework that helps clarify what properties an LLM must satisfy in order for us to safely incorporate it into empirical research.",
    "While social scientists in practice tend to treat LLMs as an all-purpose black box, in reality the model's performance will hinge critically-as our framework demonstrates-on what text the algorithm is trained on, to what text we seek to apply it, and for what purpose.",
    "Let Σ * denote the collection of strings (up to some finite length) in an alphabet with elements σ ∈Σ *.",
    "A training dataset is any collection of strings."
  ]
}